      "side": 1,
      "message": "You can make this an input parameter if you want, but the rest of the code is on lines 26 and 29 are sort of hard-coding the behavior of deferring emitting signals until the object is created. So I think you can remove this constructor parameter. On line 28 you could do\n```\nbool skipSignal{true};\nstatus(initialStatus, skipSignal);\n```\n\nDeclaring a local in this case just makes the code more clear. Otherwise there is a hardcoded true second parameter, so the reader has to wonder what that does.",
